# obsidian_superpower — Windsurf Rules

## Mandatory Rule

Before responding to ANY request — coding, debugging, planning, explanation,
research, or anything else — follow the obsidian-logging workflow.

Read the full skill file: skills/obsidian-logging/SKILL.md

There are no exceptions. The note comes before the solution, always.

## The 7-Step Workflow

0. Orient first — read obsidian/index.md (what exists), last 10 entries of obsidian/log.md (recent work), scan the active project folder (raw source context)
1. Classify the task → pick the correct obsidian/ subfolder
   - Bug/error/crash        → obsidian/Bug_Fixes/
   - Snippet/function       → obsidian/Snippets/
   - Project/feature/plan   → obsidian/Projects/
   - Daily progress/journal → obsidian/Daily_Journal/
   - Reusable prompt        → obsidian/Prompts/
   - Concept/research/docs  → obsidian/Knowledge/

2. Read the matching template from obsidian/[FOLDER]/[TEMPLATE].md

3. Fill the note — all frontmatter: title, date, language, status, tags

4. Solve the task — full solution, code, explanation, steps

5. Append the solution into the correct section of the note

6. Update obsidian/index.md — add or revise this page's one-line entry

7. Append to obsidian/log.md — format:
   ## [YYYY-MM-DD] <operation> | <title>
   - Created/Updated: obsidian/[FOLDER]/[NOTE].md
   - Key points: <brief summary>

End every response with: 📁 Save this note to: obsidian/[FOLDER]/[NOTE_TITLE].md

## Vault Structure

obsidian/
├── index.md       ← read first on every query
├── log.md         ← append-only, never overwrite
├── Knowledge/
├── Projects/
├── Snippets/
├── Bug_Fixes/
├── Prompts/
└── Daily_Journal/

## Raw Sources

The active project/work folder is the immutable source layer.
Read from it freely. Never write files outside obsidian/.
